##"Mom"-style packing goods, Wuhan University Warm Heart Call Students

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Deng Yafei, intern, Chen Zijia, _ thepaper.cn _

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A note left by a staff member at the Wuhan Polytechnic University in the student dormitory.

"Your precious desk is too big, it has been moved to the next room 1208 for temporary storage, it will not be lost, rest assured! " A Wuhan Polytechnic University student tweeted on February 24 that the school had been requisitioned as a reserve isolation point while packing up his dorm belongings, left a note like this.

On February 24, the Weibo Topic "Wuhan Polytechnic University's baby desk" attracted discussion and likes from netizens. On the same day, Wuhan Polytechnic University posted an article on its official Wechat, don't worry! Your babies will wait for you obediently.

According to the Wuhan Polytechnic University, officials, teachers and counselors at all levels of the school took matters into their own hands and carefully sorted out and stored the existing items in the students'dormitories that had been requisitioned, and connected with students on the spot to check and verify the valuables.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Before and after Wuhan Polytechnic University.

"mom-style" packing in colleges and universities

On February 18, the bed support group of Wuhan's new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued an urgent notice on "issuing a reserve task for centralized isolation points in 16 provincial universities. ".

The paper's www.thepaper.cn  found that after the announcement, colleges and universities issued micro-blogs or announcements to teachers, students and students'parents, saying that schools would properly pack students'belongings and do proper disinfection work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Staff of Wuhan Railway Vocational and technical college pack up students'belongings in their dormitory.

On Feb. 18, Shouyi College in Wuchang posted an article on its official microblog, "a letter to students, parents and teachers, " in which it said the school would learn from the good experiences and methods of other schools that have already been requisitioned rooms, carefully organize the staff to clear, pack and store the personal belongings of the students in the requisitioned dormitory.

On Feb. 19, the official Weibo Account of Wuhan Railway Vocational and Technical College said, "24 hours, 1,000 dormitories, teachers 'mother-style' packing things, baby every classmate's baby, take away everyone's untaken garbage, please rest assured, trust the teacher, trust the school. "

On the same day, the WHTCC posted an article on its official wechat called a letter from WHTCC to all teachers, students and parents of students, the university will set up a dormitory cleaning team composed of Party members, cadres and student staff, and will pack up all items in the isolation dormitory. All bags will be marked with dormitory numbers and beds, so that the whole process can be traced back, make sure nothing is damaged or lost.

On February 20, the Yangtze River Engineering Vocational and technical college posted a letter to all students of the Yangtze River Engineering Vocational and technical college on its official Wechat, "every student's clothes, books, bedding, dolls and other items will be sorted and packed by our teachers. In the process of packing, we will be sure to take care of your belongings as we do for our children who are about to travel."

Colleges and universities promise to clean up

In addition to properly packing students'belongings, colleges and universities, which act as reserve isolation points, are also committed to thorough disinfection of teachers and students.
On Feb. 18, the Wuhan University of Science and Technology posted an article on its official Wechat, Wuhan University of Science and Technology, to all teachers, students and parents of students in the school, always put the safety and health of all teachers and students in the first place. If the student dormitory is formally requisitioned, will carefully do a good job of students'personal property clearance and centralized storage work, make every effort to protect the rights and interests of students. No matter whether it is put into use or not, the site will be thoroughly, strictly and thoroughly cleaned to ensure a safe and healthy learning and living environment for teachers and students.

On Feb. 20, the Wuhan Institute of Technology posted a notice on its official wechat account, saying that the school will make every effort to ensure the safety of students'belongings, and that valuables should be registered and stored separately to ensure the safety and isolation of students'belongings. In the end, no matter whether the students'apartments are used as isolation points or not, the schools will carry out thorough cleaning and disinfection of the students'apartments to meet the standards of medical and health testing, so as to ensure that there are no hidden safety hazards in the students'apartments.

On February 18, the bed support group of Wuhan's new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued an urgent notice on "issuing a reserve task for centralized isolation points at 16 provincial universities, " which said that in order to increase the construction of isolation points, after coordination between the provincial headquarters and the provincial education department, 16 provincial universities, including the Wuhan University of Science and Technology, will be used as reserve isolation points by the Wuhan Headquarters.

A total of 15,000 university quarantine sites in 16 provinces are scheduled for completion by February 20.

The isolation rooms will be reserved in accordance with the principle of one person per bed, and the University Reserve Isolation points will commandeer buildings such as the university's stadium for the construction of a shelter hospital, except mainly for the isolation and observation of fever patients and close contacts, in principle, not for the treatment of patients with mild.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Requisition schedule of new isolation points for universities in Wuhan.

The relevant person in charge of the bed protection group said in an interview that, "The relevant departments will, in accordance with the actual situation of the epidemic, implement the reserve plan step by step according to the law and regulations according to the requirements of the epidemic situation. " The separation points of the six provincial universities are: the Hubei University of Economics, the Wuhan Textile University, the Wuhan Railway Vocational and Technical College, the Yangtze River Engineering Vocational and Technical College, the Hubei University of Technology, the Shouyi College of the People's Republic of China, the Wuhan University of Science and Technology, the Wuhan Institute of Technology, the Wuhan Institute of Technology, the Wuhan Textile University, the Wuhan Textile University, the Wuhan University of Arts and Sciences, the Wuhan Institute of Foreign Economic Relations, the Hubei University of Economics, the northern Hubei Institute of Science and Technology, and the Hubei Institute of Technology.
